<h1>Problem 2246 - 2025 Thailand MO, P10 of 10</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 9</h2>
<p>Let \(n\) be a positive integer. Show that there exist a polynomial \(P(x)\) with integer coefficient that satisfy the following
\newline - Degree of \(P(x)\) is at most \(2^n - n -1\)
\newline - \(|P(k)| = (k-1)!(2^n-k)!\) for each \(k \in \{1,2,3,\dots,2^n\}\)</p>
